parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle fails to latch or unlatch
the seat belt webbing breaks or tears
the seat belt retractor fails to lock or retract
the seat belt does not properly restrain the occupant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to come loose or break off, leading to a loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or wobbly
the steering wheel cannot be rotated
the steering column is loose
the steering wheel breaks off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake calipers can cause extended braking distances, increasing the risk of accidents, and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Spongy brake pedal
brake pedal goes to the floor
extended braking distances
uneven braking
pulling to one side while braking
grinding or screeching noise when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can cause loss of control, increased stopping distances, and accidents, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden and unexpected activation of the ABS system
brake pedal pulsation or vibration
grinding or screeching noise when applying brakes
inability to stop the vehicle in a timely manner
rear-ending another vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine, cylinder head, and other components, which can result in costly repairs, engine failure, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The temperature gauge rises to the red zone
the coolant level drops
the coolant leaks
the radiator fan fails to turn on
the vehicle overheats
the engine makes a knocking or clunking noise
the engine stalls or shuts down.
